The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Rebels shoot cop camp hand 
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Rebels shoot cop camp hand 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Midnapore, Dec. 9: Maoists today shot two men working at a police camp in Belpahari, killing one and injuring the other.        
	The deceased has been identified as 42-year-old Subol Mahato. Suresh Murmu, 30, sustained severe injuries in his head and chest. Both worked at the Kadamdiha camp in West Midnapore, around 70km from Midnapore town.         
	Subol was a pump operator and Suresh a driver.        
	District superintendent of police Manoj Verma said: The Maoists wanted to create panic by attacking people working in the police camps. That way, they believe, the local people wont do any work for the police as we are their targets. I havent yet got the details of the background of the person killed and the one injured in the firing.        
	The Maoists had come to Chirakuthi this morning from the Jharkhand side, about 3km from Kadamdiha, the police said.        
	Postmaster killed        
	Suspected Maoists shot dead the postmaster in a Purulia village, 340km west of Calcutta.        
	Asit Mondal, 45, was on his way to another village on his motorcycle when four persons shot him four times.                                                                                                                                                            
